(1651, 'Old Plain of Aldersgate Ward and St. Martins le Grand Liberty - London 1720 -', 1720, 1720, '1720', 'Blome, Richard (engraver)', 'Size Plate: 30,5 x 18 cm. Size Frame 39 x 52 cm.', 'Copper etching on paper', 'Very Good, not visioned out frame', 'When Blome died in 1705, the plates were sold to John Strype, who issued them with Blome''s name erased in his two editions of John Stow''s A Survey of the Cities of London and Westminster. The print in photography can show some reflections caused by glass. For shipping costs ask the seller.', 90, 1, 4),
