(1698, 'Ceramic figurine of a Gentleman made by Vincenzo Bertolotto in Milan. ''30/40', 1930, 1940, '1930/40', 'Vincenzo Bertolotto / Arturo Pannunzio', '30 cm. x 15 cm.', 'Ceramic', 'Exellent Condition', 'Vincenzo Bertolotti is the owner of the ceramic manufacturing company "V.B.C.M" (Vincenzo Bertolotti Ceramiche Milanesi), which has been active since the late 1920s. In the post-war years, the company changed its name to "Bertolotti Ceramiche," a manufacturer specializing in the production of stoneware, earthenware, and traditional and modern porcelain, located in Milan. The modeling of this ceramic was most likely done by Arturo Pannunzio. For shipping costs ask the seller.', 190, 2, 6),
